All three files are clean. Here's what was built:

---

**`templates/master-letter.html`** (185 lines) — Jinja2 template with 24 unique variables, 8.5x11 print-ready CSS (`@page` margins, Georgia serif, fixed confidentiality footer). Slots for `opening_paragraph`, `industry_context_paragraph`, `ebitda_narrative_paragraph`, `highlight_quote`, `hook_paragraph`, `variant_paragraph`, `closing_paragraph`, and `personalized_url`.

**`lib/letter_engine.py`** (510 lines) — Production engine:
- `LetterEngine(supabase_client).render(company_id, variant)` → returns Lob-ready HTML
- `render_all_variants(company_id)` → all three touches in one call
- 7 verticals pre-loaded with floors/ceilings/medians/drivers: `water_treatment`, `hvac`, `plumbing`, `roofing`, `pest_control`, `concrete_precast`, `flooring`
- All paragraph generators build from Supabase data — nothing hardcoded except the EBITDA benchmarks and variant copy
- Python syntax: clean

**`public/sample-letter-aquascience.html`** (201 lines) — Fully rendered letter for Larry Casey, water treatment, Wyoming RI. No Jinja2 variables. Includes a `preview-banner` div that shows on screen and disappears on print. Ready to open in a browser right now.
